cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses feature learning for challenging learning problems in domains such as speech, computer vision, and natural language processing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, given the focus on discriminative learning and the use of score-function features, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible, as they are related to the topics discussed in the paper.
